      'Use details from both sources. Write a summary of the differences between the attitudes to education presented in Source A and Source B.\n\nSource A (21st century): "Education today is a right, accessible to all regardless of background. Schools are judged on their inclusivity, their pastoral care, their ability to nurture the whole child. Every student is encouraged to find their voice."\n\nSource B (19th century): "The business of the schoolroom is discipline. A boy learns his letters not for pleasure but for duty, and the master\'s rod is as essential to the classroom as the blackboard. Sentiment has no place where character is being forged."',
